{%- comment -%}
  Starts With Tool
    Returns true or false depending if a string starts with another string.
    Checks are case sensitive.

    This works by splitting the string by the prefix. Shopify will make the 
    first element in the array be an empty string (blank) if the string does
    start with the prefix, otherwise it will not.

  Params:
    str - String to check.
    prefix - Prefix to see if the str contains.

  Outputs:
    "true" if the string starts with the prefix, otherwise "false"

  Version:
    1.0.0 - 2021/06/28
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- liquid
  assign arr = str | split: prefix

  if arr[0] == blank
    echo 'true'
  else
    echo 'false'
  endif
-%}